# CODEOWNERS — declares the three-scope boundary in a machine-readable form.
# Full map + the cross-scope rule: docs/repo-map.md
#
# Single maintainer today (@parsoFish); the GROUPING is the load-bearing signal —
# it declares "core vs data vs managed content" without moving a file. CODEOWNERS is
# last-match-wins, so more-specific Scope-3 paths below correctly override their
# Scope-2 parents.

# ── Scope 1 — Framework / seams / orchestration (the hot path) ───────────────
# Rule: never special-case a project or a specific cycle-agent.
/orchestrator/   @parsoFish
/cli/            @parsoFish
/loops/          @parsoFish
/forge-ui/       @parsoFish
/bin/            @parsoFish
/scripts/        @parsoFish

# ── Scope 2 — Cycles / agents / flows (OOTB + authoring) ─────────────────────
# Rule: never assume a particular managed project.
/skills/            @parsoFish
/studio/            @parsoFish
/brain/forge-dev/   @parsoFish
/brain/cycles/      @parsoFish

# ── Scope 3 — Projects forge develops ────────────────────────────────────────
# Rule: respect the forge↔project contract; never edit orchestrator/cli/loops.
/projects/                       @parsoFish
/brain/projects/                 @parsoFish
/docs/forge-project-contract.md  @parsoFish
/skills/forge-onboard-project/   @parsoFish

# ── Cross-cutting ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/docs/    @parsoFish
